{"type":"message","id":"b99c2dc4","parentId":"27bb93dc","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:00:40.563Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_4ca47a78-0a72-450b-8e9e-2a56b122762c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-04-12 — Day 12 of Dream Mode\n\n## Morning Brief\n\n**Session files:** `dfb1ab76-cf36-4902-a31c-354955720d97.jsonl` (Apr 12 08:00)\n**Screenshot folder:** Flushed\n\n## Resource Map Audit\n\n**Discovery:** Multiple incorrect corpus paths in MEMORY.md. Fixed during morning session.\n- AW corpus: `rag_abroadworks/clean_md/` (79 articles, not 25 in abroadworks/ folder)\n- Nava blog corpus: `rag/clean_txt/` (44 articles, was showing 22)\n- Both corrected and committed\n\n**Reminder set:** Investigate Nava corpus doubling overnight (morning brief Apr 13)\n\n## Skills Built/Updated Today\n\n### Brand Integration Skill — NEW\n- Location: `skills/brand-integration/` + `skills/brand-integration.skill`\n- Core rule: **Reveal pattern** — zero brand mentions in body, single earned reveal at section/article end\n- SEO rationale: repeated exact-match brand drops hurt SEO performance\n- 79-article corpus analysis confirmed Tiny's pattern (first-person \"we/our\", inside the business) vs others (third-party recommendation, service directory style)\n- \"AW\" abbreviation prohibited in text\n\n### Source Integration Skill — NEW\n- Location: `skills/source-integration/` + `skills/source-integration.skill`\n- Anchor text rule: **natural phrase, not article title** (critical correction applied to NC article)\n- 5 external sources confirmed: EIG state map, IRS common law, IRS topic 762, Ontario non-compete, Epstein Becker Green 2025\n- 9 internal cross-links confirmed live: abroadworks.com/blog URLs\n- SoT copied to `rag_abroadworks/drafts/Contractor Non-Competes and Termination.odt`\n\n### Article Revision Skill — NEW\n- Location: `skills/article-revision-skill/` + `skill file`\n- Workflow: SoT validation → AWAA instructions → 6-pass editor review → decision gate\n- SoT validation protocol added to both phased-outlining SKILL.md and Master SOP\n\n### SEO Content Audit (Rohit, Jun 2025) — READ\n- PDF: `SEO_Abroadworks_Rohit_23-Jun-2025_Content_Audit.pdf` (Downloads folder)\n- Confirmed: 2,000-3,000 word target, 5-15 internal links per article, meta description 140-160 chars, title 50-60 chars\n- Keyword placement: primary in H1 + first 100 words + one H2; semantic keywords throughout body\n- **Heading conflict identified:** Editorial headings for narrative logic vs SEO headings for topical signal. Resolution: ensure H2 content is keyword-adjacent enough for crawlers without sacrificing readability.\n- LSI outdated (Google confirmed not using LSI) — replaced with **semantic keywords** concept\n\n## NC Article Revision — Completed\n\n**File:** `abroadworks/article-independent-contractor-non-compete_REVISED.md`\n\n**Changes applied:**\n- H3.2.3 removed (redundant with H3.2.1 P2 after MEAL fix)\n- H3.2.2: now leads with case facts (business type, restrictions, court ruling) before analysis — $9M lands after context\n- H2.3 brand reveal: zero brand mentions in body, single earned reveal at section end (\"That is the structure AbroadWorks builds into every independent contractor agreement.\")\n- All 14 links embedded naturally (anchor text = natural phrase, not article title):\n  - 5 external: EIG, IRS common law, IRS 762, Ontario non-compete, Epstein Becker\n  - 9 internal: EOR risk, bookkeeper-risk, outsourcing-vs-offshoring, async-work, outsourcing-customer-care, offshore-vs-local-labor, AI customer service trap, offshore-bookkeeping, outsourcing-popularity\n\n**Editor skill failure logged:** Pass 2.3 claimed \"links embedded\" based on mental headcount, not file inspection. 9 internal cross-links missing. Encoding hard rule: verify actual file text for link count, not assertion.\n\n## Dusk Webapp — PENDING\n- URL: `https://204.168.204.198/` — untested since Apr 10 midnight\n- Needs verification\n\n## Awaiting Tiny Input\n\n- New skill (SEO publishing layer) — ready to build after research delivered\n- NC article: Awaiting Tiny's final review and publish go-ahead\n## Afternoon Work — Transcript Review COMPLETED\n\n**Mission accomplished:**\n- Read raw session files (not compactions) for Apr 9-12 NC article journey\n- Built composite skill at `skills/article-writing-path/` — 17KB, full journey documented\n- Updated MEMORY.md with process learnings and guardrails\n\n**What was created:**\n1. `skills/article-writing-path/SKILL.md` — complete 10-step path from keyword to published article\n2. `.skill` package — packaged and committed\n3. MEMORY.md updated — process section replaced with Article Writing Path reference\n4. Memory file updated — full journey notes captured\n\n**The 10-step path:**\nKeyword → AWAA spawn (brand reveal in brief) → H2 approval → H3 sub-headings → Canvas → Phase 5 → 6-pass review → Cross-links/sources → Publishing readiness → Final save\n\n**Key failures documented (with guardrails):**\n- AWAA system prompt compression → H3 nesting lost → flat article → 30+ min wasted\n- \"Links embedded\" false positive → 9 internal links missing → presented incomplete article\n- Building skills from memory → wrong anchor text rule → had to fix mid-session\n- Responding to nudges as decisions → built a skill when Tiny sent \"?\" \n- Chinese characters in canvas → found via hex search, not grep\n\n**Ready for Article 2 (How to Fire an Independent Contractor).**\n\n## Durable Memory Update — Post-Compaction Flush (2:56 PM UTC)\n\n### Skills Table — Updated\n\n| Skill | Location | Purpose |\n|-------|----------|---------|\n| article-writing-path | workspace skills/ | NEW — complete 10-step keyword-to-published path, every failure/guardrail encoded (17KB) |\n| article-revision-skill | workspace skills/ | Phase 5 targeted edits, structural changes, brand reveal pattern, link embedding |\n| source-integration | workspace skills/ | Natural phrase anchor text rule (1-4 